&lt;h1 id="filters-that-fight-back"&gt;Filters that Fight Back&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;August 2003&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We may be able to improve the accuracy of Bayesian spam filters by having them follow links to see what&amp;rsquo;s waiting at the other end. Richard Jowsey of death2spam now does this in borderline cases, and reports that it works well.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>